SIMPLE: indeciduous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indeciduous
<hw>In`de*cid"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not deciduous
or falling, as the leaves of trees in autumn; lasting; evergreen;
persistent; permanent; perennial. Opposite of
<ant>deciduous</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>indeciduous</qex> and unshaven locks of Apollo.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indecimable</ent>⟦br⟧
